itemDescription: English cricketer, rugby union footballer and hockey player (1888-1915)

wikipedia_page.main: Frederick Cecil Banes-Walker (19 June 1888 – 9 May 1915) was an English first-class cricketer who played five matches for Somerset County Cricket Club.  He also played rugby for Clifton Rugby Football Club, and hockey for Gloucestershire.  He was killed in action during the First World War.

link_mentions.page: List of Somerset County Cricket Club players

response: *Cecil Banes-Walker, of the 2nd Devonshire Regiment who made five first-class appearances for Somerset was killed in action aged 26 between 6:45 and 7:30 on 9 May 1915 as his battalion advanced to provide support during the Battle of Aubers Ridge.

link_mentions.page: List of cricketers who were killed during military service
